12                p.card-text.text-dark                    | "Dependent adults" covered by the law include any person residing in California between the ages of 18 and 64 who have physical or mental limitations which restrict their ability to carry out normal activities and protect their rights and specifically includes all hospital inpatients.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark                    | "Elders" covered by the law include all persons residing in California 65 years of age or older.    .form-row.col-md-12      .form-group.col-md-12          h5.text-dark Discretionary Reporting      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark                  | Those subject to the reporting obligation must reopen when, within their professional capacity of the scope of their employment; they either;      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark                  | Isolation includes :                  br                  | 1. Acts intended to prevent, and that do prevent, an elder or dependent adult from receiving mail or telephone calls.                  br                  | 2. Telling a caller of prospective visitor that an elder or dependent adult is not present, or does not wish to talk with the caller or to meet with the visitor where the statement is false, contrary to the express wishes of the elder or dependant adult from having contact with family, friends or concerned persons;                  br                  | 3. False imprisonment (as defined in Penal Code 236); and                  br                  | 4. Physical restraint of an elder or dependent adult for the purpose of preventing the person from meeting with visitors.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark                  | The above acts are subject to a rebuttal presumption that they do not constitute isolation if they are performed pursuant to the instructions of a physical who is caring for the elder or dependent adult and who gives the instructions as part of the persons medical care. Furthermore the above acts do not constitute isolation if they are performed in response to a reasonably perceived threat of danger to properly or physical safety.      .form-row.col-md-12          .form-group.col-md-12              p.card-text.text-dark                  | "Dependent adults" covered by the law include any person residing in California between the ages of 18 and 64 who have physical or mental limitations which restrict their ability to carry out normal activities and protect their rights and specifically includes all hospital inpatients.    .form-row.col-md-12        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark                    | Reports. Reports by Telephone and in writing must be made to;        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark                    | 1. The long-term care ombudsman coordinator or local law enforcement agency (the city police or County sheriff's department, or country probation's department) when the abuse is alleged to have occured in a long-term care facility; or                    br                    | 2. To the country adult protective services agency (Country Welfare Department) or a local law enforcement agency when the abuse is alleged to have occured anywhere else.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark                    | Both the telephone and written report should include unless the information is unavailable to the reporter, the name, address,telephone number and occupation of the person making the report, the name and address of the victim, the date,time and place of the incident, other details, including the reporters observation's and beliefs concerning the incident, any statement relating to the incident and the name of the individuals believed to be responsible for the incident and their connection to the victim. The written report is to be on a standardized form which should be available from country adult protective services agencies and must be sent within two working days of notice of the abuse.        .form-row.col-md-12            .form-group.col-md-12                p.card-text.text-dark                    | I Hereby attest that i understand my obligation to report elder and dependent adult abuse as described above and will fullfill this obligation.    .form-row.col-12.float-right      .form-group.col-6.float-right      .form-group.col-md-6.text-center          .card              .card-body.bg-white                  div.flex.text-center                      div#sigbox(style="width:450px;")                          input#signature(name='pg14signature' type='text' placeholder='Sign here' style="font-size:50px;")                  br                  h4.mt-0.header-title.text-center.text-dark Signature